<item>
            <title>[AMQ-2045] Unbalanced Valve usage in VMTransport.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-2045</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Valve doesn&apos;t check that its state is consistent (counters &amp;gt;= 0).  There&apos;s unbalanced increment/decrement calls in VMTransport.oneway:&lt;br/&gt;
                 enqueueValve.decrement();  //TODO unbalanced??&lt;br/&gt;
 (line ~99) &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If I balance this with a preceding enqueValve.increment() I get a deadlock in a test when the server tries to send a response message so I assume the correct fix is to remove the decrement in this VMTransports valve.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
